const title = "Whirlpool Appliance Repair, Same-Day Service Across Southern California | Same Day Appliance Repair";
const description = "Whirlpool appliance repair across LA, OC, Ventura, SB, Riverside. Refrigerator, washer (Cabrio + Duet), dryer, dishwasher, range. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Whirlpool still an American company?",
    a: "Yes, and that distinguishes it from most of its competition. Whirlpool Corporation is headquartered in Benton Harbor, Michigan, and is the largest major-appliance manufacturer in the world. Unlike GE Appliances (sold to Haier in 2016) or Samsung and LG (Korean), Whirlpool has remained American-owned with significant US manufacturing, Clyde, Ohio (washers); Marion, Ohio (dishwashers); Findlay, Ohio (dishwashers); Tulsa, Oklahoma (cooking); Amana, Iowa (refrigeration). Whirlpool also owns several familiar US-market brands: Maytag, KitchenAid, Amana, and JennAir. Engineering and parts supply chains for all five brands run through Whirlpool Corp, which is why a tech who knows Whirlpool inside and out usually knows the others by extension."
  },
  {
    q: "Is there a class action settlement on my Whirlpool refrigerator?",
    a: "Possibly, and worth checking before you pay for a repair. Whirlpool, Maytag, KitchenAid, and JennAir Side-by-Side and French Door refrigerators manufactured between 2018 and 2021 are subject to a class action settlement covering a wire-harness defect that causes intermittent or complete failure of the ice maker, ice dispenser, water dispenser, and control panel. The wires routing through the freezer-side door hinge assembly fatigue and break from repeated door movement. Settlement deadline for valid claims is November 2, 2026. If your unit fits the manufacture date and shows any of the listed symptoms, file the claim form before paying out-of-pocket for the repair. We help homeowners verify eligibility on diagnostic visits, model number, serial, manufacture date, and the specific failure pattern determine whether the work routes through Whirlpool or through us."
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my Whirlpool refrigerator ice maker keep freezing up?",
    a: "Three common causes, in diagnostic order. (1) Water inlet tube freezing, the small fill tube that delivers water from the inlet valve to the ice maker tray can freeze if water pressure is low, the valve is leaking slightly between cycles, or the freezer is set too cold (below 0°F). Thawing the tube clears the symptom; addressing the root cause prevents recurrence. (2) Door gasket failure pulling humid kitchen air into the freezer compartment, where it condenses and freezes around the ice maker assembly. Door gasket replacement runs $180-$280. (3) Defrost system fault, heater, thermostat, or sensor, causing frost buildup that shouldn't occur. Defrost component replacement $185-$345 depending on which item failed. About 40% of ice maker freeze-up calls trace to the inlet tube; another 35% to the gasket; balance to defrost system or the ice maker itself."
  },
  {
    q: "What does an F01 error mean on my Whirlpool dryer?",
    a: "F01 on Whirlpool Duet, Cabrio, and most modern Whirlpool dryers indicates a main control board (CCU) fault, usually an internal short or relay failure on the board itself. Common cause: a power surge or extended power outage damaging the board's electronics. Diagnostic order: (1) full reset, unplug the dryer (or kill the breaker) for 5-10 minutes, then power back on. About 15% of F01 codes clear at this step. (2) If F01 returns, the CCU needs replacement ($345-$525 with labor). On Duet dryers, the CCU is mounted on the back and accessible without major disassembly; on top-loaders the access is from the back panel. We confirm the part number against the model on diagnostic, Duet, Cabrio, and Duet Sport variants use different boards even within the same generation."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Whirlpool Cabrio and Duet washers?",
    a: "Two different architectures. Cabrio is Whirlpool's high-efficiency top-load family (no agitator on most models, impeller-driven), launched mid-2000s through the 2010s, still in service across millions of homes. Cabrio service tree centers on the lid lock/lid switch (frequent failure year 3-6), the basket spin bearing (year 8-10), the suspension rod kit (year 9+), and the main control board. Duet is the front-load family, Whirlpool's entry into the European-style front-load market, launched in the 2000s. Duet service tree includes drain pump (year 5-8), door boot (year 8-10), bearing service (year 8-12; bearing + drum seal as a set, $585-$880 with labor), and main control board (CCU). Duet washers are generally more energy- and water-efficient; Cabrios are simpler-architecture and faster cycle times. Both are reliable platforms when serviced at the right intervals."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Whirlpool, Maytag, KitchenAid, and JennAir really the same company?",
    a: "Same parent company, different positioning. Whirlpool Corporation owns all four brands and shares engineering platforms across them, many Maytag washers and dryers are mechanically identical to Whirlpool models with different cosmetic trim and model badging. KitchenAid is positioned as the premium kitchen-appliance tier (refrigerators, dishwashers, ranges, cooktops, mixers); JennAir is Whirlpool's ultra-premium / luxury tier competing with Sub-Zero and Wolf for built-in refrigeration and pro-style cooking. Amana is the value-tier brand. From a parts-and-service standpoint, our trucks carry common Whirlpool/Maytag wear items and we cross-reference KitchenAid and JennAir parts through the same Whirlpool distribution. Service depth on the premium tiers (KitchenAid built-in, JennAir luxury) requires specific tech training; basic Whirlpool and Maytag service is bread-and-butter work for our team."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you carry Whirlpool OEM parts on the truck?",
    a: "Yes, Whirlpool is among the brands we stock most heavily because it's the highest-volume on our service mix. Common items always on the truck: refrigerator door gaskets, ice maker assemblies, water inlet valves, evaporator fan motors, defrost heaters and thermostats; washer lid switches (top-load), drain pumps, water inlet valves, drive belts; dryer thermal fuses, thermistors, drum belts, idler pulleys, heating elements; range surface igniters, oven bake/broil elements, oven temperature sensors. Less common parts, main control boards (CCU on Duet, central control on Cabrio), specific KitchenAid/JennAir components, premium dishwasher control boards, come from authorized Whirlpool distribution, usually 1-3 day lead. Wire-harness assemblies for the 2018-2021 class action refrigerators are also stocked for paid out-of-warranty repairs when the claim window has closed for a particular customer."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Whirlpool appliance repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when work is approved. Common Whirlpool repairs: refrigerator door gasket $180-$280; refrigerator water inlet valve $185-$285; refrigerator ice maker assembly $245-$385; refrigerator main control board $345-$525; washer lid switch / lid lock (top-load) $145-$215; washer drain pump $245-$385; washer drive belt + pulley (top-load) $185-$285; washer door boot (Duet front-load) $285-$425; washer main control board (CCU) $345-$525; dryer thermal fuse + vent inspection $145-$245; dryer heating element $285-$425; dryer drum belt + idler $195-$295; dryer CCU (F01 fix) $345-$525; dishwasher drain pump $245-$385; dishwasher control board $345-$525; range surface igniter $145-$215; oven bake element $185-$285; oven temperature sensor $145-$215. Front-load washer bearing + drum seal as a set $585-$880. KitchenAid and JennAir parts run 15-30% above base Whirlpool pricing."
  }
];

