    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool WRS588FIHZ Side-by-Side, Sherman Oaks</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Ice maker stopped producing, water dispenser intermittent, control panel LED flickering. Owner reported the issues started gradually over 3-4 weeks.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Manufacture date 2019, within the 2018-2021 class action window for the wire-harness defect. Symptoms (multi-system failure: ice maker + dispenser + control panel) matched the documented pattern. Confirmed harness damage at the freezer-side door hinge during inspection.</p>
        <p><strong>Outcome:</strong> Recommended customer file the class action settlement claim before authorizing paid repair. Customer filed; claim qualified; repair routed through Whirlpool's authorized network at no cost to customer.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost:</strong> $89 diagnostic only. Customer saved approximately $580 by routing through the settlement.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool WTW8500DW Cabrio top-load, Pasadena</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Washer fills, agitates, but stalls before spin. Cycle progress LED stops at the same point every wash. No error code displayed.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Lid lock assembly intermittent, common Cabrio failure year 4-6. Switch ohms-out reading inconsistent. Drive system tested fine; drain pump tested fine.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Lid lock / lid switch assembly replacement with OEM Whirlpool part (in stock on the truck). Verified normal lid-lock engagement and full cycle progression on test wash.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $185 total. Same-day, 50 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Whirlpool WED8000DW Duet electric dryer, Rancho Cucamonga</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Dryer displaying F01 code at startup. Won't run any cycle. Customer reported a recent thunderstorm power flicker the night before.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Full power-cycle reset performed (10 minutes off). F01 returned within seconds of power-up. CCU diagnostic confirmed internal short on a relay, typical post-power-surge damage pattern.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> CCU (main control board) replacement with OEM Whirlpool part (1-day lead from authorized distribution; return visit). Verified normal startup, full cycle test, F01 cleared.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost &amp; time:</strong> $445 total. Two-visit repair (diagnostic + part install). Total time on-site across both visits: 2 hours.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

